> What could be better than a tender, flaky pastry filled with fall fruit flavors? Two blossoms are filled with apples and cinnamon, topped with a buttery cinnamon-oat crumble, and two are filled with a cozy medley of apples, blackberries, raspberries, and wild blueberries! They're irresistibly sweet, satisfying, and all-around delicious! When you're ready to dig in, simply warm them up. You can even enjoy them chilled or at room temperature—we're big fans of the "less-is-more" philosophy.

> We highly recommend serving with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

Use @Apple Berry Blossoms{2} and @Crumble Crunch Apple Blossom{2}.

> Keep frozen until ready to eat; best if used within 7 days. Remove plastic wrap from trays; microwave until warmed through, ~{50-60%seconds}. Do not overheat.

> Oven alternative: Keep frozen or refrigerated until ready to eat; best if used within 7 days. If frozen, thaw in the refrigerator (at 40 degrees) overnight or at room temperature for ~{2-3%hours} before baking. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 350 degrees. Remove plastic wrap from trays; place on a #baking sheet{} and bake until warmed through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Oven times may vary.